text: The University of Michigan College of Engineering is the engineering section of the University of Michigan in Ann Arbor. With 6,351 undergraduate and 3,331 graduate students as of 2012, the College of Engineering is one of the largest engineering schools in the United States. In several ranking systems, the college is ranked as one of the top ten engineering schools in the nation. == References == Category:University of Michigan campus Category:Engineering schools Category:1854 establishments in the United States Category:1850s establishments in Michigan
